			<p class="plamen_body_text">
				Plamen Mitrikov has spent his entire career in structured credit. Prior to establishing Foundation View Capital, Mr. Mitrikov was an Executive Director in Morgan Stanley’s New Issue CLO group, responsible for all aspects of CLO structuring and execution. Mr. Mitrikov specialized in bringing to market newer CLO platforms, and also spent considerable time analyzing and marketing CLO equity. Prior to Morgan Stanley, Mr. Mitrikov served as Co-Head of Structured Credit at Princeridge, where he was in charge of CLO new issue, and ABS/Trust Preferred CDO trading. From 2006 to 2011, Mr. Mitrikov served as an Executive Vice President of RAIT Investment Trust, a Philadelphia headquartered commercial real estate mortgage REIT. From April 2003 to February 2006, Mr. Mitrikov held various positions, including that of Vice President and Director, in the structured credit products group at Merrill Lynch specializing in the origination and execution of Trust Preferred and ABS CDOs. Prior to joining Merrill Lynch, Mr. Mitrikov worked in the new issue CDO group at Credit Suisse First Boston.
