  					Andrew K. Davilman is the COO of Foundation View Capital Management. He also serves as a Managing Director of IFMI’s Asset Management business and as a Managing Director, Sales and Special Projects with J.V.B. Financial Group, LLC, IFMI’s broker-dealer subsidiary. Mr. Davilman spent 16 years at Goldman, Sachs & Co. in a variety of positions. As a Managing Director, from 2006 to 2010, Mr. Davilman founded and co-ran the Structured Credit Sales desk. Before that Mr. Davilman worked in Institutional Mortgage sales from 1998 to 2006. From 1994 to 1998, Mr. Davilman traded MBS derivatives including Inverse Floaters, Inverse IOs, IOs and POs, and CMO Residuals. Before joining Goldman, Sachs, Mr. Davilman traded MBS derivatives at Lehman Brothers from 1989 to 1995. Mr. Davilman has expertise in credit default swaps, collateralized debt obligations and collateralized loan obligations, as well as other derivatives and cash instruments typically traded across the fixed income universe. Mr. Davilman holds an A.B. in Religion from Dartmouth College and holds an M.B.A from Stanford University’s Graduate School of Business.  
